<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870806-0099 </DOCNO><HL> Central Capital SaysIts Offer for TradersClass A Attracted 95%</HL><DD> 08/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> T.CEH TTG.ASTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Central Capital Corp. said that 95% of Traders Group Ltd.'s Class A non-voting shares were tendered under Central's offer for Traders, in a transaction valued at 292.3 million Canadian dollars ($220.1 million).    Central Capital, a financial-services concern based in Halifax, Nova Scotia, said that about 3,925,000 Traders Class A shares were tendered. Holders of Traders shares will receive 4.75 Central Capital Class A shares plus five dollars for each Traders Class A share.    Yesterday, in trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange, Central Capital Class A stock closed at 14.625 dollars, off 12.5 cents.    Central said it will use provisions of Canadian corporate law to acquire the remaining 5% of Traders Group Class A shares.    Traders, a Toronto-based financial-services concern, has interests in a trust company, insurance companies and other financial concerns.    Central's offer for Traders' Class B voting shares remains open until next Tuesday. Under that offer, holders will receive 222.50 dollars and four Central Capital preferred shares, valued at 25 dollars each, for each B share.    Traders has about 387,000 Class B shares outstanding, placing the value of that offer at 124.8 million dollars. Central already owns 88% of Traders' Class B shares. </TEXT></DOC>